Change has been successfully merged
I assume you want lineMsg (errMsg is never assigned a value and can be removed)
Done
may as well update this line
Added 9elements GmbH
nit:  the docs still want the { } around single line if statements
Done
can be const
Done

I know you just copied this from the other file, but since implicit conversion is recommended against (https://github.com/nlohmann/json#implicit-conversions), and you're also doing the .get<std::string>() calls below, may as well change these to all use get<>() to be consistent.
Done
Any update on the change? Is it ready to be merged?
I'd like Patrick to review it as well.
Some minor suggestions.
Do you also need to add fs.copyfile for phosphor-multi-gpio-presence.json?

I'm assuming that phosphor-multi-gpio-presence.json is an example config and should not be used in production. I can't tell why `phosphor-multi-gpio-monitor.json` is installed.
I personally prefer a failing service due to missing config file, rather than a running service that uses an example config file.
Any update on the issue?
Was just checking. I agree with your statement.
Wouldn't we want to know what the error was here?
Added errno to the error message.

It isn't obvious to me why you need to delete the move operators.  A side-effect of this is that in the main function you end up keeping a vector of unique_ptrs rather than the objects themselves.  Can we enable the move-operator and refrain from using the extra indirection of unique_ptr?
Implemented the move constructor and dropped use of unique_ptrs.
"file not found" isn't the only reason that an open can fail, right?
Fixed the error message.
A few more minor nits.  Sorry for the slow response; been traveling this week.

I tried to use the phosphor-multi-gpio-presence by get the patch set and add the phosphor-multi-gpio-presence.json.
But I got below error and the service stops.
```
root@MB:~# journalctl | grep -i "multi-gpio-presence"
Apr 03 20:59:23 MB phosphor-multi-gpio-presence[567]: GPIO Line presence-cpu0 [ ActiveLow] monitoring started
Apr 03 20:59:23 MB phosphor-multi-gpio-presence[567]: Updating inventory present property value to True, path: /system/chassis/motherboard/CPU_1
Apr 03 20:59:26 MB phosphor-multi-gpio-presence[567]: Error in mapper call to get service name, path: /xyz/openbmc_project/inventory, interface: xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Manager, error: sd_bus_call: xyz.openbmc_project.Common.Error.ResourceNotFound: The resource is not found.
Apr 03 20:59:26 MB phosphor-multi-gpio-presence[567]: terminate called after throwing an instance of 'sdbusplus::xyz::openbmc_project::Common::Error::InternalFailure'
Apr 03 20:59:26 MB phosphor-multi-gpio-presence[567]:   what():  xyz.openbmc_project.Common.Error.InternalFailure: The operation failed internally.
Apr 03 20:59:26 MB phosphor-multi-gpio-presence[567]: The operation failed internally.
Apr 03 20:59:42 MB systemd[1]: phosphor-multi-gpio-presence.service: Main process exited, code=dumped, status=6/ABRT
Apr 03 20:59:42 MB systemd[1]: phosphor-multi-gpio-presence.service: Failed with result 'core-dump'.
```
I tried to check the existing of the xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Manager service.
```
root@MB:~# busctl call xyz.openbmc_project.ObjectMapper /xyz/openbmc_project/object_mapper xyz.openbmc_project.ObjectMapper GetObject sas /xyz/openbmc_project/inventory 1 xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Manager
a{sas} 1 "xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Manager" 5 "org.freedesktop.DBus.Introspectable" "org.freedesktop.DBus.ObjectManager" "org.freedesktop.DBus.Peer" "org.freedesktop.DBus.Properties" "xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Manager"
root@MB:~#
```
Do I miss any things?

I wonder why the DRIVER option does not support?
I saw that option in phosphor-gpio-presence source:
https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-gpio-monitor/blob/d1a35410e9ae0e17d00c16b07410f76565dd1dcc/presence/main.cpp#L82
And it is using 
https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/blob/master/meta-ibm/recipes-phosphor/gpio/phosphor-gpio-monitor/obmc/gpio/phosphor-power-supply-0.conf
I have no use for that feature, but it could be implemented here as well.
Because the patch set is ready to Merge, maybe it is better to add new patch set to support drivers configuration on top of this patch set.
It isn't obvious to me why the log call got dropped between PS7 and now?
The async operation is canceled in the introduced move constructor. The move constructor also moves the strings that were printed here, causing only garbage to appear in the log.

I think you're saying that in some cases (specifically of cancellation) you expect to get an `ec` but at that point (specifically in the case of cancellation), `this` is no longer valid?  Shouldn't you look for the `ec` that indicates cancellation then and only skip printing out the log in that case?  Dropping the log for every error seems like we're missing potentially necessary debug.

At a minimum, I think you can print out `ec.message()`, right?
Added back the logging on error case.
Generally we use 'ERRNO' for errnos and 'ERROR' for exceptions.
Done

`
Wants=mapper-wait@-xyz-openbmc_project-inventory.service
After=mapper-wait@-xyz-openbmc_project-inventory.service
`
should be added to make sure the service will start after xyz.openbmc_project.inventory.manager.service
Done

Should we include
`
[Install]
RequiredBy=multi-user.target
`
Done

Does the phosphor-multi-gpio-presence service create the InterfaceAdded, PropertyChanged D-Bus signal when it adds/Updated new D-Bus inventory path? I tested the patch set with below configuration to create CPU_1/CPU_2 Presence D-Bus inventory path.
```
[
    {
        "Name": "CPU_1",
        "LineName": "presence-cpu0",
        "ActiveLow": true,
        "Inventory": "/system/chassis/motherboard/CPU_1"
    },
    {
        "Name": "CPU_2",
        "LineName": "presence-cpu1",
        "ActiveLow": true,
        "Inventory": "/system/chassis/motherboard/CPU_2"
    }
]
I can see that the inventory paths are added as expected.
```
        `-/xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/chassis
          `-/xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/chassis/motherboard
            |-/xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/chassis/motherboard/CPU_1
            `-/xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/chassis/motherboard/CPU_2
```

This added D-Bus inventory paths
 then will be used by ADC sensor service in dbus-sensor repo to create the corresponding sensors base on the existing of CPU_1/CPU_2 inventory path. (The sensor with CPURequired=1 only are created when `Present` property in the inventory path /xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/chassis/motherboard/CPU_2 is True.)
 https://github.com/openbmc/dbus-sensors/blob/436c5bdb25c775138c901dc707f203c076adcb97/src/ADCSensorMain.cpp#L403
 https://github.com/openbmc/dbus-sensors/blob/436c5bdb25c775138c901dc707f203c076adcb97/src/ADCSensorMain.cpp#L377

Can you share your dbus-monitor command which you used to watch the `notify` and `property changed` signals?
I'm running
```
dbus-monitor --system type=signal,path=/xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/chassis/motherboard,interface=xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item
```
while calling
`systemctl start phosphor-multi-gpio-presence.service`
with new phosphor-multi-gpio-presence.json to create some new dbus path for PSU. I can see the new D-BUS path in the tree of `xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Manager` service. But still does not see the signal in dbus-monitor window.

```
busctl tree xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Manager
`-/xyz

    `-/xyz/openbmc_project/inventory
